The paper deals with audio-visual correspondence and cross-modal retrieval, which are topics related to computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the localization of objects in images based on audio signals, which falls under the sub-category of sound and music computing (cs.SD). The use of unlabelled video for training the network also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG).
